00:51:04.830 --> 00:51:07.980 align:middle line:90%
I had been working a lot.

00:51:07.980 --> 00:51:13.000 align:middle line:84%
I worked at Harvard Medical
School, but one day I woke up

00:51:13.000 --> 00:51:16.660 align:middle line:84%
and I was just in
incredible pain.

00:51:16.660 --> 00:51:21.950 align:middle line:84%
And I would say that the
day before that, in a way,

00:51:21.950 --> 00:51:24.020 align:middle line:90%
was the last day of my life.

00:51:24.020 --> 00:51:28.360 align:middle line:84%
I couldn't get out of
bed because of pain.

00:51:28.360 --> 00:51:31.570 align:middle line:84%
I had gone to a series
of very top doctors.

00:51:31.570 --> 00:51:34.870 align:middle line:84%
I was sent to specialist
after specialist.

00:51:34.870 --> 00:51:38.410 align:middle line:84%
And they kept
making predictions,

00:51:38.410 --> 00:51:40.840 align:middle line:90%
and they kept coming out wrong.

00:51:40.840 --> 00:51:42.400 align:middle line:84%
Someone said to
me, you have to be

00:51:42.400 --> 00:51:44.300 align:middle line:90%
your own doctor at one point.

00:51:44.300 --> 00:51:46.720 align:middle line:84%
And so I started
doing my own research,

00:51:46.720 --> 00:51:48.940 align:middle line:90%
and they took a blood test.

00:51:48.940 --> 00:51:52.210 align:middle line:84%
And they checked almost
every box on the list,

00:51:52.210 --> 00:51:56.740 align:middle line:84%
and I asked the rheumatologist
can we check for scleroderma?

00:51:56.740 --> 00:51:59.920 align:middle line:84%
Because luckily, unlike a
lot of these other diseases,

00:51:59.920 --> 00:52:01.420 align:middle line:90%
there's a test for it.

00:52:01.420 --> 00:52:05.180 align:middle line:84%
And after six months, I
found my own diagnosis,

00:52:05.180 --> 00:52:10.560 align:middle line:84%
which is scleroderma, an
autoimmune disease, which

00:52:10.560 --> 00:52:13.260 align:middle line:84%
hardens the connective
tissue in your body, which

00:52:13.260 --> 00:52:16.140 align:middle line:90%
holds your body together.

00:52:16.140 --> 00:52:18.930 align:middle line:90%
So I slowly turned into a mummy.

00:52:18.930 --> 00:52:24.870 align:middle line:84%
>> About three years down the
road of hard work and virtually

00:52:24.870 --> 00:52:28.500 align:middle line:84%
imbalanced lifestyle-- it's
work, work, work, study, study,

00:52:28.500 --> 00:52:29.370 align:middle line:90%
study--

00:52:29.370 --> 00:52:32.040 align:middle line:90%
one night it all exploded.

00:52:32.040 --> 00:52:35.390 align:middle line:84%
I basically woke up in
the morning about 5:00 AM,

00:52:35.390 --> 00:52:37.980 align:middle line:84%
and just feeling so
bizarre and weird,

00:52:37.980 --> 00:52:40.740 align:middle line:84%
and it was like everything
was spinning around.

00:52:40.740 --> 00:52:43.860 align:middle line:84%
I basically was
losing my breath.

00:52:43.860 --> 00:52:46.915 align:middle line:84%
So later on, I realized that
it was a severe panic attack.

00:52:46.915 --> 00:52:48.290 align:middle line:84%
I didn't know what
to make of it.

00:52:48.290 --> 00:52:51.390 align:middle line:84%
It was basically
so overwhelming.

00:52:51.390 --> 00:52:54.440 align:middle line:84%
And then basically that
shifted everything in my life.

00:52:54.440 --> 00:52:56.690 align:middle line:90%
I lost sleep completely.

00:52:56.690 --> 00:52:59.690 align:middle line:84%
The anxiety attacks were
going one after another--

00:52:59.690 --> 00:53:01.760 align:middle line:84%
I mean, like an
avalanche, day after day.

00:53:01.760 --> 00:53:04.700 align:middle line:84%
Suffering during the day, not
sleeping during the night,

00:53:04.700 --> 00:53:07.310 align:middle line:90%
thinking the craziest thoughts.

00:53:07.310 --> 00:53:09.590 align:middle line:84%
The thoughts were
coming by themselves.

00:53:09.590 --> 00:53:12.590 align:middle line:84%
Things really started
getting weird.

00:53:12.590 --> 00:53:15.020 align:middle line:84%
My blood pressure
dropped like 60 to 80.

00:53:15.020 --> 00:53:17.720 align:middle line:90%
My pulse went up over 100.

00:53:17.720 --> 00:53:21.655 align:middle line:84%
Always tired and not be able to
relax, or sleep, or anything.

00:53:21.655 --> 00:53:23.030 align:middle line:84%
So finally I just
realized, yeah,

00:53:23.030 --> 00:53:24.260 align:middle line:90%
I need to go to the doctor.

00:53:24.260 --> 00:53:25.190 align:middle line:90%
And it's interesting.

00:53:25.190 --> 00:53:28.150 align:middle line:84%
Oddly enough, the doctor looked
at me and said, you're fine.

00:53:28.150 --> 00:53:30.260 align:middle line:84%
You're just going--
like many people

00:53:30.260 --> 00:53:32.270 align:middle line:90%
are going through stress.

00:53:32.270 --> 00:53:34.640 align:middle line:84%
Many immigrants do
go through that,

00:53:34.640 --> 00:53:36.120 align:middle line:90%
but everything's fine with you.

00:53:36.120 --> 00:53:39.130 align:middle line:84%
You just need to
get it together.

00:53:39.130 --> 00:53:40.580 align:middle line:90%
He didn't offer me anything.

00:53:40.580 --> 00:53:42.050 align:middle line:84%
He didn't offer
me any counseling.

00:53:42.050 --> 00:53:44.040 align:middle line:84%
He didn't offer me
anything at all.

00:53:44.040 --> 00:53:46.370 align:middle line:84%
It was like I left
the office virtually

00:53:46.370 --> 00:53:49.580 align:middle line:84%
with the same knowledge
that I entered the office.

00:53:49.580 --> 00:53:52.970 align:middle line:84%
I just realized that I no
longer can support life.

00:53:52.970 --> 00:53:55.250 align:middle line:84%
I can no longer
be in the family.

00:53:55.250 --> 00:53:57.530 align:middle line:84%
So I declared to
my wife that I'm

00:53:57.530 --> 00:53:58.970 align:middle line:84%
leaving, that we
need to separate,

00:53:58.970 --> 00:54:01.220 align:middle line:84%
because it's taking
too much on me.

00:54:01.220 --> 00:54:04.700 align:middle line:84%
I totally started losing
it, started getting into all

00:54:04.700 --> 00:54:06.560 align:middle line:90%
sorts of conflicts at work.

00:54:06.560 --> 00:54:07.370 align:middle line:90%
They let me go.

00:54:07.370 --> 00:54:10.960 align:middle line:84%
I worked for the bank for
four years, a very good place.

00:54:10.960 --> 00:54:14.870 align:middle line:84%
I went for welfare and
started getting food

00:54:14.870 --> 00:54:16.160 align:middle line:90%
from Salvation Army.

00:54:16.160 --> 00:54:18.170 align:middle line:84%
And if you know
any notion of what

00:54:18.170 --> 00:54:21.060 align:middle line:84%
it is to be out of your
mind, that was what I was.

00:54:21.060 --> 00:54:23.040 align:middle line:90%
It was like a mental hospital.

00:54:23.040 --> 00:54:23.840 align:middle line:90%
People are there.

00:54:23.840 --> 00:54:26.290 align:middle line:90%
They are walking.

00:54:26.290 --> 00:54:28.640 align:middle line:84%
Lights are there,
but nobody's home.

00:54:28.640 --> 00:54:32.980 align:middle line:84%
>> I found myself by age
11 sneaking into the bar,

00:54:32.980 --> 00:54:35.540 align:middle line:84%
and pouring a little bit of
this and a little bit of that.

00:54:35.540 --> 00:54:39.230 align:middle line:84%
Then I started with weed,
and that got into cocaine.

00:54:39.230 --> 00:54:42.540 align:middle line:84%
I came back to Toronto
and was introduced

00:54:42.540 --> 00:54:44.660 align:middle line:84%
to-- was looking
to score cocaine

00:54:44.660 --> 00:54:46.100 align:middle line:90%
and was introduced to heroin.

00:54:46.100 --> 00:54:47.390 align:middle line:90%
And that was really--

00:54:47.390 --> 00:54:49.370 align:middle line:84%
that I would say of
my drug of choice.

00:54:49.370 --> 00:54:52.770 align:middle line:84%
Everything else
went by the wayside.

00:54:52.770 --> 00:54:55.370 align:middle line:84%
I wasn't interested in
more alcohol and cocaine.

00:54:55.370 --> 00:54:58.730 align:middle line:84%
As my addiction progressed,
it was very easy

00:54:58.730 --> 00:55:01.940 align:middle line:84%
for me to slip
into prostitution.

00:55:01.940 --> 00:55:03.980 align:middle line:84%
I was not high functioning--
definitely not.

00:55:03.980 --> 00:55:06.320 align:middle line:84%
That was my primary
relationship--

00:55:06.320 --> 00:55:09.050 align:middle line:84%
100%-- was my
relationship with my drug.

00:55:09.050 --> 00:55:12.590 align:middle line:84%
I could only facilitate
that by having relationships

00:55:12.590 --> 00:55:14.840 align:middle line:90%
that made that possible.

00:55:14.840 --> 00:55:15.890 align:middle line:90%
>> School ended.

00:55:15.890 --> 00:55:18.920 align:middle line:84%
Everything ended, and
that became my life.

00:55:18.920 --> 00:55:26.720 align:middle line:84%
It ended up me getting arrested,
and I got put on methadone.

00:55:26.720 --> 00:55:32.930 align:middle line:84%
Being in methadone
clinics for 17, 18 years,

00:55:32.930 --> 00:55:37.250 align:middle line:84%
I didn't really see
anybody getting off of it.

00:55:37.250 --> 00:55:39.920 align:middle line:84%
It is widely prescribed,
and I didn't see anybody

00:55:39.920 --> 00:55:41.540 align:middle line:84%
getting off of it
without going back

00:55:41.540 --> 00:55:47.490 align:middle line:84%
on either some kind of either
prescription opiate or street

00:55:47.490 --> 00:55:48.290 align:middle line:90%
drug.

00:55:48.290 --> 00:55:52.100 align:middle line:84%
They were going to do a year
long thing for me, which

00:55:52.100 --> 00:55:55.340 align:middle line:84%
was like four months
or three months

00:55:55.340 --> 00:55:59.060 align:middle line:84%
to build me up to a place that
would hold me, and then keep me

00:55:59.060 --> 00:56:02.045 align:middle line:84%
there for six months,
and then three months

00:56:02.045 --> 00:56:02.920 align:middle line:90%
to take me off of it.

00:56:02.920 --> 00:56:07.852 align:middle line:84%
It keeps the drug user in
an active form of addiction,

00:56:07.852 --> 00:56:09.560 align:middle line:84%
because you have to
wake up every morning

00:56:09.560 --> 00:56:13.160 align:middle line:90%
and take it to feel normal.

00:56:13.160 --> 00:56:16.550 align:middle line:84%
That one year turned into
many, many, many years.

00:56:16.550 --> 00:56:19.670 align:middle line:84%
With addiction, you have to
be at a point of readiness,

00:56:19.670 --> 00:56:23.330 align:middle line:84%
and most people are forced into
going on methadone because they

00:56:23.330 --> 00:56:26.720 align:middle line:84%
can't afford their drug anymore,
or they're in legal trouble,

00:56:26.720 --> 00:56:29.000 align:middle line:84%
or they're going to
lose their child.

00:56:29.000 --> 00:56:31.497 align:middle line:84%
So it's not them making
a conscious decision

00:56:31.497 --> 00:56:32.330 align:middle line:90%
that, you know what?

00:56:32.330 --> 00:56:36.490 align:middle line:84%
I've reached a point of
willingness, and readiness,

00:56:36.490 --> 00:56:40.250 align:middle line:84%
and this is the way that
I can get to clarity.

00:56:40.250 --> 00:56:44.870 align:middle line:84%
I've been clean and
sober since August 11,

00:56:44.870 --> 00:56:47.930 align:middle line:90%
2005 besides the methadone.

00:56:47.930 --> 00:56:50.660 align:middle line:84%
I got off street
drugs and alcohol.

00:56:50.660 --> 00:56:54.320 align:middle line:84%
>> From what I understand,
you get maybe 10 years maximum

00:56:54.320 --> 00:56:57.830 align:middle line:84%
to live, and it's a
very painful way to go.

00:56:57.830 --> 00:57:01.610 align:middle line:84%
I was in tremendous pain,
and I was bedridden.

00:57:01.610 --> 00:57:04.310 align:middle line:84%
I traveled by
stretcher by ambulance

00:57:04.310 --> 00:57:08.840 align:middle line:84%
for three to four
years, and I was

00:57:08.840 --> 00:57:10.040 align:middle line:90%
told that there was no hope.

00:57:10.040 --> 00:57:13.160 align:middle line:84%
I think at one point I
was taking 32 pills a day.

00:57:13.160 --> 00:57:14.780 align:middle line:90%
I knew I was going to die.

00:57:14.780 --> 00:57:17.580 align:middle line:84%
I was very close to death
for a very long time.

00:57:17.580 --> 00:57:19.590 align:middle line:90%
And the pain was tremendous.

00:57:19.590 --> 00:57:22.220 align:middle line:84%
I didn't sleep for
maybe two years.

00:57:22.220 --> 00:57:24.920 align:middle line:84%
Even tucking in a sheet
was too much weight.

00:57:24.920 --> 00:57:27.320 align:middle line:84%
So I was sort of like a
cadaver, and they would just

00:57:27.320 --> 00:57:29.390 align:middle line:90%
lay the sheet over me.

00:57:29.390 --> 00:57:33.280 align:middle line:84%
I contacted a place
in the United States

00:57:33.280 --> 00:57:36.797 align:middle line:84%
