my bed, without help.

01:01:05.600 --> 01:01:11.060 align:middle line:90%
I managed to acquire ayahuasca.

01:01:11.060 --> 01:01:13.940 align:middle line:84%
I had spoken with
Dr. Gabor Maté,

01:01:13.940 --> 01:01:17.930 align:middle line:84%
who has had patients
with scleroderma before,

01:01:17.930 --> 01:01:23.510 align:middle line:84%
and he was able to give me some
advice to help me stay as safe

01:01:23.510 --> 01:01:28.410 align:middle line:84%
as possible while I was doing
it, but I just couldn't move.

01:01:28.410 --> 01:01:31.970 align:middle line:84%
>> I was reaching out to
all different doctors,

01:01:31.970 --> 01:01:35.627 align:middle line:84%
head of psychiatry here, head
of addictions at this hospital.

01:01:35.627 --> 01:01:37.460 align:middle line:84%
And they were all telling
me the same thing.

01:01:37.460 --> 01:01:38.752 align:middle line:90%
Well, you're on a smaller dose.

01:01:38.752 --> 01:01:41.390 align:middle line:90%
Don't taper anymore.

01:01:41.390 --> 01:01:44.100 align:middle line:84%
Lisa, please covet
your recovery.

01:01:44.100 --> 01:01:46.370 align:middle line:90%
Covet how far you've come.

01:01:46.370 --> 01:01:49.160 align:middle line:90%
And I knew that I couldn't.

01:01:49.160 --> 01:01:50.130 align:middle line:90%
I couldn't do it.

01:01:50.130 --> 01:01:54.110 align:middle line:84%
